name: John Putman
text: Food was delicious. They have a new deal: $6 for a personal pan pizza, bread sticks, and a drink. Service was okay. May Jesus bless you!

name: Jason Johnston
text: Stopped in on the way home to Memphis. Excellent everything. Our waitress was the best. Didn't catch her name, probably fortyish, dark haired woman was so nice. She filled us in on their personal pan, breadsticks and drink combo. Which is a steal! I'd really recommend eating here.

name: Karen Moudy
text: Clean, fast,  friendly service, buffet was well stocked. Was busy but not so busy that that couldn't take time to tell you about what they had and what they recommend.

name: Jennifer Bills
text: If i could give them a zero i would! This service was horrible! And the pizza wasn't much better.! I wouldn't recommend this Pizza Hut to anyone!

name: Cindi Wade-Mitchell
text: Food on buffet was fresh. Servers were on top of our needs. Servers were friendly. Meal was reasonably priced. One of our favorite places to dine.

name: Jaclyn Mayo
text: My husband and I came to eat and ordered Pepsi to drink. We were served 20 oz bottles. Never offered a cup with ice or anything. The waitress was terribly rude and acted as if we were an inconvenience to her. We will NOT go back.

name: Marcia Briggs
text: Good, friendly service and the pizzas were pretty good.

name: Sherry Pierce
text: Food good. Person serving us inexperienced. Bathroom nasty.

name: Thomas Brooks
text: Out of dr.pepper and pepsi, sweet tea had turned decided on water. Food was decent and service was good.

name: James Frazier
text: Try the pan style backyard bbq chicken pizza. Amazing!

name: Ixil Pierce
text: It's pretty much your run of the mill Pizza hut. The employees are really nice and they keep the place clean.

name: Sierra Betterman
text: Still good pizza but my wife and I had to wait over an hour for 5 breadsticks and they were not even busy. They just forgot.

name: Virginia 'Joy' 'Belder' Smith
text: I had Pizza Hut last night. I called & placed an order for 3 large 1 topping pizzas for $8.00 ea. for carry out. 1Pepparoni, 1 Cheese, & 1 Thin Crust Sausage. The order was ready wen we got there. However, the young cashier kinda like â€¦More

name: Steve Clark
text: It is what it is. Pizza was good service was ok.

name: Lisa Hubbard
text: Great service! Good food!

name: eugene jones
text: Food was not fresh.

name: dean griffith
text: Mediocre food, poor phone call in service quit going there

name: thomas Duck
text: The place wasn't very clean

name: Teri Castro
text: Great!

name: Stephen Parker
text: Don't dare going in any later than 1:15 pm for the lunch buffet. I basically got yelled at. They told me I couldn't get the buffet, even though I had 15 minutes left, and there was some old pizza still out.

name: Mackenzie Marlow
text: Sucks

name: Sherry Lynn Boothe
text: poor quality of food

name: Gail Wallace
text: Very long wait past time to pick up.

name: Jennifer Choate
text: Good customer service

name: Erica Dolan
text: Slow service and staff
